event: tool_result
data: {"name":"web_search","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"query\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"num_results\":10,\"results\":[{\"title\":\"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities.\"},{\"title\":\"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST\",\"url\":\"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf\",\"snippet\":\"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems.\"},{\"title\":\"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org\",\"url\":\"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf\",\"snippet\":\"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in\"},{\"title\":\"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy.\"},{\"title\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub\",\"url\":\"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/\",\"snippet\":\"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively.\"},{\"title\":\"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne\",\"url\":\"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US.\"},{\"title\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance\",\"url\":\"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle.\"},{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10\",\"snippet\":\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ...\"},{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)\",\"url\":\"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3\",\"snippet\":\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems.\"},{\"title\":\"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance\",\"url\":\"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/\",\"snippet\":\"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance.\"}],\"source\":\"duckduckgo-html\",\"tip\":\"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\"}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"query":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework","num_results":10,"results":[{"title":"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities."},{"title":"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf","snippet":"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems."},{"title":"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org","url":"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf","snippet":"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in"},{"title":"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework","url":"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy."},{"title":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub","url":"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/","snippet":"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively."},{"title":"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne","url":"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/","snippet":"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US."},{"title":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance","url":"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle."},{"title":"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)","url":"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10","snippet":"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ..."},{"title":"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)","url":"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3","snippet":"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems."},{"title":"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance","url":"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/","snippet":"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance."}],"source":"duckduckgo-html","tip":"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result"},"isError":false},"toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01AXQ7hdSqL9ufSks8Zvr5vZ","executionTimeMs":857,"targetServer":"openagentic_web","timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:31.421Z"}

