data: {"messageId":"E9MO_lG05WO-JboYzVepB","role":"tool","content":"{\n  \"content\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"text\",\n      \"text\": \"{\\\"success\\\":true,\\\"query\\\":\\\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework\\\",\\\"num_results\\\":10,\\\"results\\\":[{\\\"title\\\":\\\"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities.\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems.\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy.\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively.\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US.\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle.\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ...\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems.\\\"},{\\\"title\\\":\\\"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/\\\",\\\"snippet\\\":\\\"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance.\\\"}],\\\"source\\\":\\\"duckduckgo-html\\\",\\\"tip\\\":\\\"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\\\"}\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"structuredContent\": {\n    \"success\": true,\n    \"query\": \"NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\n    \"num_results\": 10,\n    \"results\": [\n      {\n        \"title\": \"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST\",\n        \"url\": \"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework\",\n        \"snippet\": \"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST\",\n        \"url\": \"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf\",\n        \"snippet\": \"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org\",\n        \"url\": \"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf\",\n        \"snippet\": \"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\n        \"url\": \"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\n        \"snippet\": \"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub\",\n        \"url\": \"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/\",\n        \"snippet\": \"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne\",\n        \"url\": \"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/\",\n        \"snippet\": \"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance\",\n        \"url\": \"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\n        \"snippet\": \"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)\",\n        \"url\": \"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10\",\n        \"snippet\": \"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ...\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)\",\n        \"url\": \"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3\",\n        \"snippet\": \"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems.\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"title\": \"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance\",\n        \"url\": \"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/\",\n        \"snippet\": \"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance.\"\n      }\n    ],\n    \"source\": \"duckduckgo-html\",\n    \"tip\": \"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\"\n  },\n  \"isError\": false\n}","toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01AXQ7hdSqL9ufSks8Zvr5vZ","timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:31.636Z","source":"database","confirmed":true}

