data: {"calls":[{"id":"toolu_bdrk_0138aEKZ9nDNKSBwewd2GUdZ","name":"web_search","tool":"web_search","toolName":"web_search","serverId":"openagentic_web","serverName":"openagentic_web","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"query":"FedRAMP AI ML authorization requirements 2025 2026","num_results":10},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"query\":\"FedRAMP AI ML authorization requirements 2025 2026\",\"num_results\":10,\"results\":[{\"title\":\"FedRAMP AI\",\"url\":\"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/\",\"snippet\":\"Effective Date: Monday, August 18,2025In response to formal recommendations from theFedRAMPBoard (by electronic vote) and the Chief Information Officers Council (by electronic notification),FedRAMPwill begin prioritizing certainAIcloud services forFedRAMPauthorization. This page explains the criteria and process for prioritization as required by theFedRAMPAuthorizationAct ...\"},{\"title\":\"GSA and FedRAMP Announce Major Initiative: Prioritizing 20x ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/newsroom/news-releases/gsa-fedramp-prioritize-20x-authorizations-for-ai-08252025\",\"snippet\":\"In a letter to theFedRAMPBoard on August 12,2025, the CIO Council urgently requestedFedRAMPprioritize theauthorizationofAI-based cloud services that provide access to conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers.\"},{\"title\":\"FedRAMP ATO for AI Platforms: Hidden Requirements You Must Meet\",\"url\":\"https://elevateconsult.com/insights/fedramp-ato-for-ai-platforms-hidden-requirements-you-must-meet/\",\"snippet\":\"Explore theFedRAMPATO process forAIplatforms: discover hiddenrequirements, costs, timelines, and how to achieve Moderate or Highauthorizationfor federal contracts.\"},{\"title\":\"Getting ahead of CMMC, FedRAMP and AI Compliance before it gets ahead ...\",\"url\":\"https://federalnewsnetwork.com/commentary/2025/12/getting-ahead-of-cmmc-fedramp-and-ai-compliance-before-it-gets-ahead-of-you/\",\"snippet\":\"If2025felt like a whirlwind for regulatory compliance, you're not imagining it. Between the finalization of Cybersecurity Model Maturity Certification 2.0 rules, the launch ofFedRAMP's20x initiative promising fasterauthorizations, and newAIgovernancerequirementsfrom the Office of Management and Budget and the National Institute of Standards and Technology, organizations working ...\"},{\"title\":\"Why FedRAMP Adherence Matters for AI in Government—and How Microsoft ...\",\"url\":\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/publicsectorblog/why-fedramp-adherence-matters-for-ai-in-government%E2%80%94and-how-microsoft-makes-it-pr/4448008\",\"snippet\":\"Below is a practical guide to using MicrosoftAIcapabilities (Copilot for Microsoft 365, Copilot Studio, and AzureAIFoundry) in a way that keeps you aligned toFedRAMPrequirements, plus the Microsoft security and compliance tools that help you sustainauthorization.\"},{\"title\":\"What New Changes Are Coming to FedRAMP in 2026?\",\"url\":\"https://www.ignyteplatform.com/blog/fedramp/new-changes-fedramp-2026/\",\"snippet\":\"Learn about the adjustments toFedRAMPin2026, focusing onAI, computing advances, and the streamlinedauthorizationprocess of the 20x program's new phase.\"},{\"title\":\"GSA launches pilot to streamline FedRAMP for AI products\",\"url\":\"https://www.nextgov.com/acquisition/2025/08/gsa-launches-pilot-streamline-fedramp-ai-products/407672/\",\"snippet\":\"TheFedRAMP20x initiative will automate some approvals for what the General Services Administration is calling \\\"conversationalAI\\\" if certain security conditions are met.\"},{\"title\":\"GSA & FedRAMP Accelerate AI Cloud Services Authorization\",\"url\":\"https://executivegov.com/articles/gsa-fedramp-ai-cloud-services-authorization\",\"snippet\":\"GSA andFedRAMPlaunched an initiative supporting America'sAIAction Plan that fast-tracksauthorizationofAI-powered cloud services.\"},{\"title\":\"AI in Action: How GSA is Transforming Federal Services\",\"url\":\"https://www.gsa.gov/blog/2025/12/31/ai-in-action-how-gsa-is-transforming-federal-services\",\"snippet\":\"FedRAMPdelivers on the White House'sAIAction Plan priority to enableAIadoption in government by prioritizing theauthorizationof conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers. We're on track to complete the first threeAIPrioritizationFedRAMP20x Lowauthorizationsin January2026!\"},{\"title\":\"FedRAMP Authorization in 2026: What Software Companies Need to Know ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.convox.com/blog/fedramp-authorization-2026-guide-saas-companies\",\"snippet\":\"Feb 18,2026- A practical guide toFedRAMPauthorizationin2026covering real timelines, costs, the new 20x program, and a 12-month readiness checklist for SaaS companies considering the government market.\"}],\"source\":\"duckduckgo-html\",\"tip\":\"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\"}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"query":"FedRAMP AI ML authorization requirements 2025 2026","num_results":10,"results":[{"title":"FedRAMP AI","url":"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/","snippet":"Effective Date: Monday, August 18,2025In response to formal recommendations from theFedRAMPBoard (by electronic vote) and the Chief Information Officers Council (by electronic notification),FedRAMPwill begin prioritizing certainAIcloud services forFedRAMPauthorization. This page explains the criteria and process for prioritization as required by theFedRAMPAuthorizationAct ..."},{"title":"GSA and FedRAMP Announce Major Initiative: Prioritizing 20x ...","url":"https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/newsroom/news-releases/gsa-fedramp-prioritize-20x-authorizations-for-ai-08252025","snippet":"In a letter to theFedRAMPBoard on August 12,2025, the CIO Council urgently requestedFedRAMPprioritize theauthorizationofAI-based cloud services that provide access to conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers."},{"title":"FedRAMP ATO for AI Platforms: Hidden Requirements You Must Meet","url":"https://elevateconsult.com/insights/fedramp-ato-for-ai-platforms-hidden-requirements-you-must-meet/","snippet":"Explore theFedRAMPATO process forAIplatforms: discover hiddenrequirements, costs, timelines, and how to achieve Moderate or Highauthorizationfor federal contracts."},{"title":"Getting ahead of CMMC, FedRAMP and AI Compliance before it gets ahead ...","url":"https://federalnewsnetwork.com/commentary/2025/12/getting-ahead-of-cmmc-fedramp-and-ai-compliance-before-it-gets-ahead-of-you/","snippet":"If2025felt like a whirlwind for regulatory compliance, you're not imagining it. Between the finalization of Cybersecurity Model Maturity Certification 2.0 rules, the launch ofFedRAMP's20x initiative promising fasterauthorizations, and newAIgovernancerequirementsfrom the Office of Management and Budget and the National Institute of Standards and Technology, organizations working ..."},{"title":"Why FedRAMP Adherence Matters for AI in Government—and How Microsoft ...","url":"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/publicsectorblog/why-fedramp-adherence-matters-for-ai-in-government%E2%80%94and-how-microsoft-makes-it-pr/4448008","snippet":"Below is a practical guide to using MicrosoftAIcapabilities (Copilot for Microsoft 365, Copilot Studio, and AzureAIFoundry) in a way that keeps you aligned toFedRAMPrequirements, plus the Microsoft security and compliance tools that help you sustainauthorization."},{"title":"What New Changes Are Coming to FedRAMP in 2026?","url":"https://www.ignyteplatform.com/blog/fedramp/new-changes-fedramp-2026/","snippet":"Learn about the adjustments toFedRAMPin2026, focusing onAI, computing advances, and the streamlinedauthorizationprocess of the 20x program's new phase."},{"title":"GSA launches pilot to streamline FedRAMP for AI products","url":"https://www.nextgov.com/acquisition/2025/08/gsa-launches-pilot-streamline-fedramp-ai-products/407672/","snippet":"TheFedRAMP20x initiative will automate some approvals for what the General Services Administration is calling \"conversationalAI\" if certain security conditions are met."},{"title":"GSA & FedRAMP Accelerate AI Cloud Services Authorization","url":"https://executivegov.com/articles/gsa-fedramp-ai-cloud-services-authorization","snippet":"GSA andFedRAMPlaunched an initiative supporting America'sAIAction Plan that fast-tracksauthorizationofAI-powered cloud services."},{"title":"AI in Action: How GSA is Transforming Federal Services","url":"https://www.gsa.gov/blog/2025/12/31/ai-in-action-how-gsa-is-transforming-federal-services","snippet":"FedRAMPdelivers on the White House'sAIAction Plan priority to enableAIadoption in government by prioritizing theauthorizationof conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers. We're on track to complete the first threeAIPrioritizationFedRAMP20x Lowauthorizationsin January2026!"},{"title":"FedRAMP Authorization in 2026: What Software Companies Need to Know ...","url":"https://www.convox.com/blog/fedramp-authorization-2026-guide-saas-companies","snippet":"Feb 18,2026- A practical guide toFedRAMPauthorizationin2026covering real timelines, costs, the new 20x program, and a 12-month readiness checklist for SaaS companies considering the government market."}],"source":"duckduckgo-html","tip":"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result"},"isError":false},"status":"completed","startTime":1771633648808,"endTime":1771633651636,"duration":2828,"timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:31.636Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01AXQ7hdSqL9ufSks8Zvr5vZ","name":"web_search","tool":"web_search","toolName":"web_search","serverId":"openagentic_web","serverName":"openagentic_web","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"query":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework","num_results":10},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"query\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"num_results\":10,\"results\":[{\"title\":\"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities.\"},{\"title\":\"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST\",\"url\":\"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf\",\"snippet\":\"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems.\"},{\"title\":\"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org\",\"url\":\"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf\",\"snippet\":\"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in\"},{\"title\":\"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy.\"},{\"title\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub\",\"url\":\"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/\",\"snippet\":\"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively.\"},{\"title\":\"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne\",\"url\":\"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US.\"},{\"title\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance\",\"url\":\"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle.\"},{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10\",\"snippet\":\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ...\"},{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)\",\"url\":\"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3\",\"snippet\":\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems.\"},{\"title\":\"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance\",\"url\":\"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/\",\"snippet\":\"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance.\"}],\"source\":\"duckduckgo-html\",\"tip\":\"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\"}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"query":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework","num_results":10,"results":[{"title":"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities."},{"title":"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf","snippet":"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems."},{"title":"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org","url":"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf","snippet":"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in"},{"title":"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework","url":"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy."},{"title":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub","url":"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/","snippet":"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively."},{"title":"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne","url":"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/","snippet":"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US."},{"title":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance","url":"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle."},{"title":"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)","url":"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10","snippet":"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ..."},{"title":"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)","url":"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3","snippet":"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems."},{"title":"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance","url":"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/","snippet":"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance."}],"source":"duckduckgo-html","tip":"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result"},"isError":false},"status":"completed","startTime":1771633648808,"endTime":1771633651636,"duration":2828,"timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:31.636Z"}],"totalCalls":2,"round":1}

