data: {"messageId":"RpI6JaGsAYZ-nozXjcGXq","role":"assistant","content":"Both pages fetched successfully. The NIST page was lightweight (mostly navigation links), so let me also grab the deeper **FedRAMP 2026 changes** article and the **Elevate Consult hidden requirements** article for richer detail, then store findings.","timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:43.500Z","toolCalls":[{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01VZ9Wg2fMyyTekcmygAZrcu","type":"function","function":{"name":"web_fetch","arguments":"{\"url\":\"https://www.ignyteplatform.com/blog/fedramp/new-changes-fedramp-2026/\",\"max_length\":30000}"}},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01Tt813Jg4PNFL38VeuJbU2Z","type":"function","function":{"name":"web_fetch","arguments":"{\"url\":\"https://elevateconsult.com/insights/fedramp-ato-for-ai-platforms-hidden-requirements-you-must-meet/\",\"max_length\":30000}"}}],"mcpCalls":[{"id":"toolu_bdrk_0138aEKZ9nDNKSBwewd2GUdZ","name":"web_search","tool":"web_search","toolName":"web_search","serverId":"openagentic_web","serverName":"openagentic_web","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"query":"FedRAMP AI ML authorization requirements 2025 2026","num_results":10},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"query\":\"FedRAMP AI ML authorization requirements 2025 2026\",\"num_results\":10,\"results\":[{\"title\":\"FedRAMP AI\",\"url\":\"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/\",\"snippet\":\"Effective Date: Monday, August 18,2025In response to formal recommendations from theFedRAMPBoard (by electronic vote) and the Chief Information Officers Council (by electronic notification),FedRAMPwill begin prioritizing certainAIcloud services forFedRAMPauthorization. This page explains the criteria and process for prioritization as required by theFedRAMPAuthorizationAct ...\"},{\"title\":\"GSA and FedRAMP Announce Major Initiative: Prioritizing 20x ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/newsroom/news-releases/gsa-fedramp-prioritize-20x-authorizations-for-ai-08252025\",\"snippet\":\"In a letter to theFedRAMPBoard on August 12,2025, the CIO Council urgently requestedFedRAMPprioritize theauthorizationofAI-based cloud services that provide access to conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers.\"},{\"title\":\"FedRAMP ATO for AI Platforms: Hidden Requirements You Must Meet\",\"url\":\"https://elevateconsult.com/insights/fedramp-ato-for-ai-platforms-hidden-requirements-you-must-meet/\",\"snippet\":\"Explore theFedRAMPATO process forAIplatforms: discover hiddenrequirements, costs, timelines, and how to achieve Moderate or Highauthorizationfor federal contracts.\"},{\"title\":\"Getting ahead of CMMC, FedRAMP and AI Compliance before it gets ahead ...\",\"url\":\"https://federalnewsnetwork.com/commentary/2025/12/getting-ahead-of-cmmc-fedramp-and-ai-compliance-before-it-gets-ahead-of-you/\",\"snippet\":\"If2025felt like a whirlwind for regulatory compliance, you're not imagining it. Between the finalization of Cybersecurity Model Maturity Certification 2.0 rules, the launch ofFedRAMP's20x initiative promising fasterauthorizations, and newAIgovernancerequirementsfrom the Office of Management and Budget and the National Institute of Standards and Technology, organizations working ...\"},{\"title\":\"Why FedRAMP Adherence Matters for AI in Government—and How Microsoft ...\",\"url\":\"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/publicsectorblog/why-fedramp-adherence-matters-for-ai-in-government%E2%80%94and-how-microsoft-makes-it-pr/4448008\",\"snippet\":\"Below is a practical guide to using MicrosoftAIcapabilities (Copilot for Microsoft 365, Copilot Studio, and AzureAIFoundry) in a way that keeps you aligned toFedRAMPrequirements, plus the Microsoft security and compliance tools that help you sustainauthorization.\"},{\"title\":\"What New Changes Are Coming to FedRAMP in 2026?\",\"url\":\"https://www.ignyteplatform.com/blog/fedramp/new-changes-fedramp-2026/\",\"snippet\":\"Learn about the adjustments toFedRAMPin2026, focusing onAI, computing advances, and the streamlinedauthorizationprocess of the 20x program's new phase.\"},{\"title\":\"GSA launches pilot to streamline FedRAMP for AI products\",\"url\":\"https://www.nextgov.com/acquisition/2025/08/gsa-launches-pilot-streamline-fedramp-ai-products/407672/\",\"snippet\":\"TheFedRAMP20x initiative will automate some approvals for what the General Services Administration is calling \\\"conversationalAI\\\" if certain security conditions are met.\"},{\"title\":\"GSA & FedRAMP Accelerate AI Cloud Services Authorization\",\"url\":\"https://executivegov.com/articles/gsa-fedramp-ai-cloud-services-authorization\",\"snippet\":\"GSA andFedRAMPlaunched an initiative supporting America'sAIAction Plan that fast-tracksauthorizationofAI-powered cloud services.\"},{\"title\":\"AI in Action: How GSA is Transforming Federal Services\",\"url\":\"https://www.gsa.gov/blog/2025/12/31/ai-in-action-how-gsa-is-transforming-federal-services\",\"snippet\":\"FedRAMPdelivers on the White House'sAIAction Plan priority to enableAIadoption in government by prioritizing theauthorizationof conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers. We're on track to complete the first threeAIPrioritizationFedRAMP20x Lowauthorizationsin January2026!\"},{\"title\":\"FedRAMP Authorization in 2026: What Software Companies Need to Know ...\",\"url\":\"https://www.convox.com/blog/fedramp-authorization-2026-guide-saas-companies\",\"snippet\":\"Feb 18,2026- A practical guide toFedRAMPauthorizationin2026covering real timelines, costs, the new 20x program, and a 12-month readiness checklist for SaaS companies considering the government market.\"}],\"source\":\"duckduckgo-html\",\"tip\":\"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\"}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"query":"FedRAMP AI ML authorization requirements 2025 2026","num_results":10,"results":[{"title":"FedRAMP AI","url":"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/","snippet":"Effective Date: Monday, August 18,2025In response to formal recommendations from theFedRAMPBoard (by electronic vote) and the Chief Information Officers Council (by electronic notification),FedRAMPwill begin prioritizing certainAIcloud services forFedRAMPauthorization. This page explains the criteria and process for prioritization as required by theFedRAMPAuthorizationAct ..."},{"title":"GSA and FedRAMP Announce Major Initiative: Prioritizing 20x ...","url":"https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/newsroom/news-releases/gsa-fedramp-prioritize-20x-authorizations-for-ai-08252025","snippet":"In a letter to theFedRAMPBoard on August 12,2025, the CIO Council urgently requestedFedRAMPprioritize theauthorizationofAI-based cloud services that provide access to conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers."},{"title":"FedRAMP ATO for AI Platforms: Hidden Requirements You Must Meet","url":"https://elevateconsult.com/insights/fedramp-ato-for-ai-platforms-hidden-requirements-you-must-meet/","snippet":"Explore theFedRAMPATO process forAIplatforms: discover hiddenrequirements, costs, timelines, and how to achieve Moderate or Highauthorizationfor federal contracts."},{"title":"Getting ahead of CMMC, FedRAMP and AI Compliance before it gets ahead ...","url":"https://federalnewsnetwork.com/commentary/2025/12/getting-ahead-of-cmmc-fedramp-and-ai-compliance-before-it-gets-ahead-of-you/","snippet":"If2025felt like a whirlwind for regulatory compliance, you're not imagining it. Between the finalization of Cybersecurity Model Maturity Certification 2.0 rules, the launch ofFedRAMP's20x initiative promising fasterauthorizations, and newAIgovernancerequirementsfrom the Office of Management and Budget and the National Institute of Standards and Technology, organizations working ..."},{"title":"Why FedRAMP Adherence Matters for AI in Government—and How Microsoft ...","url":"https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/publicsectorblog/why-fedramp-adherence-matters-for-ai-in-government%E2%80%94and-how-microsoft-makes-it-pr/4448008","snippet":"Below is a practical guide to using MicrosoftAIcapabilities (Copilot for Microsoft 365, Copilot Studio, and AzureAIFoundry) in a way that keeps you aligned toFedRAMPrequirements, plus the Microsoft security and compliance tools that help you sustainauthorization."},{"title":"What New Changes Are Coming to FedRAMP in 2026?","url":"https://www.ignyteplatform.com/blog/fedramp/new-changes-fedramp-2026/","snippet":"Learn about the adjustments toFedRAMPin2026, focusing onAI, computing advances, and the streamlinedauthorizationprocess of the 20x program's new phase."},{"title":"GSA launches pilot to streamline FedRAMP for AI products","url":"https://www.nextgov.com/acquisition/2025/08/gsa-launches-pilot-streamline-fedramp-ai-products/407672/","snippet":"TheFedRAMP20x initiative will automate some approvals for what the General Services Administration is calling \"conversationalAI\" if certain security conditions are met."},{"title":"GSA & FedRAMP Accelerate AI Cloud Services Authorization","url":"https://executivegov.com/articles/gsa-fedramp-ai-cloud-services-authorization","snippet":"GSA andFedRAMPlaunched an initiative supporting America'sAIAction Plan that fast-tracksauthorizationofAI-powered cloud services."},{"title":"AI in Action: How GSA is Transforming Federal Services","url":"https://www.gsa.gov/blog/2025/12/31/ai-in-action-how-gsa-is-transforming-federal-services","snippet":"FedRAMPdelivers on the White House'sAIAction Plan priority to enableAIadoption in government by prioritizing theauthorizationof conversationalAIengines that are designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers. We're on track to complete the first threeAIPrioritizationFedRAMP20x Lowauthorizationsin January2026!"},{"title":"FedRAMP Authorization in 2026: What Software Companies Need to Know ...","url":"https://www.convox.com/blog/fedramp-authorization-2026-guide-saas-companies","snippet":"Feb 18,2026- A practical guide toFedRAMPauthorizationin2026covering real timelines, costs, the new 20x program, and a 12-month readiness checklist for SaaS companies considering the government market."}],"source":"duckduckgo-html","tip":"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result"},"isError":false},"status":"completed","startTime":1771633648808,"endTime":1771633651636,"duration":2828,"timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:31.636Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01AXQ7hdSqL9ufSks8Zvr5vZ","name":"web_search","tool":"web_search","toolName":"web_search","serverId":"openagentic_web","serverName":"openagentic_web","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"query":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework","num_results":10},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"query\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"num_results\":10,\"results\":[{\"title\":\"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities.\"},{\"title\":\"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST\",\"url\":\"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf\",\"snippet\":\"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems.\"},{\"title\":\"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org\",\"url\":\"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf\",\"snippet\":\"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in\"},{\"title\":\"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy.\"},{\"title\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub\",\"url\":\"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/\",\"snippet\":\"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively.\"},{\"title\":\"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne\",\"url\":\"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US.\"},{\"title\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance\",\"url\":\"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework\",\"snippet\":\"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle.\"},{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10\",\"snippet\":\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ...\"},{\"title\":\"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)\",\"url\":\"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3\",\"snippet\":\"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems.\"},{\"title\":\"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance\",\"url\":\"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/\",\"snippet\":\"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance.\"}],\"source\":\"duckduckgo-html\",\"tip\":\"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result\"}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"query":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework","num_results":10,"results":[{"title":"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"On July 26, 2024,NISTreleasedNIST-AI-600-1, Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework: Generative Artificial Intelligence Profile . The profile can help organizations identify uniquerisksposed by generativeAIand proposes actions for generativeAIriskmanagementthat best aligns with their goals and priorities."},{"title":"PDFArtificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1 - NIST","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf","snippet":"The Artificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a living document that provides guidance for managingrisksand trustworthiness ofAIsystems. It consists of four functions: Govern, Map, Measure, and Manage, and covers nine characteristics of trustworthyAIsystems."},{"title":"PDFAI Risk Management Framework | NIST - data.aclum.org","url":"https://data.aclum.org/storage/2025/01/NIST_www_nist_gov_itl_ai-risk-management-framework.pdf","snippet":"August 18, 2022NISTis seeking comments on a second draft of theNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF). TheAIRMF is intended for voluntary use in"},{"title":"Learn All About the NIST AI Risk Management Framework","url":"https://auditboard.com/blog/what-is-the-nist-ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) is a voluntary standard published in January 2023 byNIST, an agency of the U.S. Department of Commerce dedicated to promoting innovation and developing standards across the economy."},{"title":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework Playbook - Digital Government Hub","url":"https://digitalgovernmenthub.org/library/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-playbook/","snippet":"TheAIRMF Playbook offers organizations detailed, voluntary guidance for implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkto map, measure, manage, and governAIriskseffectively."},{"title":"What is the NIST AI Risk Management Framework? - SentinelOne","url":"https://www.sentinelone.com/cybersecurity-101/cybersecurity/nist-ai-risk-management-framework/","snippet":"TheNISTArtificial IntelligenceRiskManagementFramework(AIRMF) provides organizations with a structured, flexible, and repeatable process to identify, measure, and manage the uniquerisksposed byAIsystems. This voluntaryframeworkwas released in January of 2023 and has become the most widely adoptedAIgovernance standard in the US."},{"title":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework: A simple guide to smarter AI governance","url":"https://www.diligent.com/resources/blog/nist-ai-risk-management-framework","snippet":"TheNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkis a voluntary, widely recognized guide developed by the National Institute of Standards and Technology to help organizations managerisksthroughout the artificial intelligence (AI) lifecycle."},{"title":"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (AI RMF 1.0)","url":"https://www.nist.gov/publications/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf-10","snippet":"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems. TheFrameworkis intended to be voluntary, rights-preserving ..."},{"title":"Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework (Ai Rmf 1.0)","url":"https://www.govinfo.gov/app/details/GOVPUB-C13-ef6882c6bd970bc733de394f469ea3f3","snippet":"Abstract As directed by the National Artificial Intelligence Initiative Act of 2020 (P.L. 116-283), the goal of theAIRMF is to offer a resource to the organizations designing, developing, deploying, or usingAIsystems to help manage the manyrisksofAIand promote trustworthy and responsible development and use ofAIsystems."},{"title":"Nist ai risk management framework | Roadmap to Compliance","url":"https://blog.rsisecurity.com/nist-ai-risk-management-framework-guide/","snippet":"Discover a step-by-step guide to implementing theNISTAIRiskManagementFrameworkfor trustworthyAIand effectiveriskgovernance."}],"source":"duckduckgo-html","tip":"Use web_fetch to read the full content of any interesting result"},"isError":false},"status":"completed","startTime":1771633648808,"endTime":1771633651636,"duration":2828,"timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:31.636Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01DXfr6JiSAUF2a7cCmqkghK","name":"web_fetch","tool":"web_fetch","toolName":"web_fetch","serverId":"openagentic_web","serverName":"openagentic_web","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"url":"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/","max_length":50000},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"cached\":false,\"url\":\"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/\",\"title\":\"FedRAMP AI\",\"content\":\"![Mountain background](/mountain_abstract.svg)\\n\\n# FedRAMP AI Prioritization\\n\\n**Effective Date: Monday, August 18, 2025**\\n\\nIn response to formal recommendations from the FedRAMP Board (by electronic vote) and the Chief Information Officers Council (by electronic notification), FedRAMP will begin prioritizing certain AI cloud services for FedRAMP authorization. This page explains the criteria and process for prioritization as required by the FedRAMP Authorization Act.\\n\\n## Prioritization Criteria\\n\\nFedRAMP is now prioritizing the authorization of AI-based cloud services that provide access to conversational AI engines designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers. To ensure this prioritization in the best interest of the federal government, such services must meet all of the following criteria to be prioritized:\\n\\n* Offer enterprise-grade features including single-sign on, SCIM provisioning, role-based access control, and real-time analytics\\n* Guarantee data separation and protection; any model information from training on customer data will not leave the customer environment without customer authorization\\n* Establish demand from at least five CFO Act agencies or be specifically recommended by the CIO Council\\n* Be available for government use via the GSA Multiple Award Schedule program\\n* Be able to meet the requirements for a FedRAMP 20x authorization within two months of acceptance for prioritization\\n\\n## Prioritization Process\\n\\nCloud service providers who receive prioritization under this criteria will follow a separate process similar to the FedRAMP 20x Phase One pilot:\\n\\n* Cloud service providers who meet this criteria should reach out directly to the FedRAMP Director via [pete@fedramp.gov](mailto:pete@fedramp.gov) to discuss next steps.\\n* Providers will be required to meet all [Initial Submission Requirements for the 20x Phase One pilot](/20x/phase-one).\\n* Providers will receive additional pre-submission support from FedRAMP.\\n* 20xP1 pilot submissions will be accepted outside the standard submission window; there is no deadline for submission.\\n* Providers will receive additional post-authorization support from FedRAMP and the FedRAMP Board to encourage adoption.\\n\\n## List of Prioritized Services\\n\\n### [ChatGPT Enterprise and API Platform, by OpenAI](https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2533155773)\\n\\n* *On track for FedRAMP 20x Low authorization by January 2026*\\n\\n### [Gemini for Government, by Google](https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604952026)\\n\\n* *On track for FedRAMP 20x Low authorization by January 2026*\\n\\n### [Perplexity Enterprise Pro for Government, by Perplexity AI, Inc.](https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604643715)\\n\\n* *On track for FedRAMP 20x Low authorization by January 2026*\\n\\nAdditional services will be added to this list as they meet the prioritization criteria and begin working on FedRAMP 20x.\\n\\n[![GSA logo](/gsa-star-mark-whtlogo.svg)](https://www.gsa.gov/)\\n\\nFedRAMP.gov\\n\\nAn official website of the GSA’s [Technology Transformation Services](https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/organization/federal-acquisition-service/technology-transformation-services)\\n\\nLooking for U.S. government information and services?\\n\\n[Visit USA.gov](https://www.usa.gov/)\\n\\n Top\",\"content_length\":3243,\"links\":[{\"text\":\"Initial Submission Requirements for the 20x Phase One pilot\",\"url\":\"https://www.fedramp.gov/20x/phase-one\"},{\"text\":\"ChatGPT Enterprise and API Platform, by OpenAI\",\"url\":\"https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2533155773\"},{\"text\":\"Gemini for Government, by Google\",\"url\":\"https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604952026\"},{\"text\":\"Perplexity Enterprise Pro for Government, by Perplexity AI, Inc.\",\"url\":\"https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604643715\"},{\"text\":\"Technology Transformation Services\",\"url\":\"https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/organization/federal-acquisition-service/technology-transformation-services\"},{\"text\":\"Visit USA.gov\",\"url\":\"https://www.usa.gov/\"}]}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"cached":false,"url":"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/","title":"FedRAMP AI","content":"![Mountain background](/mountain_abstract.svg)\n\n# FedRAMP AI Prioritization\n\n**Effective Date: Monday, August 18, 2025**\n\nIn response to formal recommendations from the FedRAMP Board (by electronic vote) and the Chief Information Officers Council (by electronic notification), FedRAMP will begin prioritizing certain AI cloud services for FedRAMP authorization. This page explains the criteria and process for prioritization as required by the FedRAMP Authorization Act.\n\n## Prioritization Criteria\n\nFedRAMP is now prioritizing the authorization of AI-based cloud services that provide access to conversational AI engines designed for routine and repeated use by federal workers. To ensure this prioritization in the best interest of the federal government, such services must meet all of the following criteria to be prioritized:\n\n* Offer enterprise-grade features including single-sign on, SCIM provisioning, role-based access control, and real-time analytics\n* Guarantee data separation and protection; any model information from training on customer data will not leave the customer environment without customer authorization\n* Establish demand from at least five CFO Act agencies or be specifically recommended by the CIO Council\n* Be available for government use via the GSA Multiple Award Schedule program\n* Be able to meet the requirements for a FedRAMP 20x authorization within two months of acceptance for prioritization\n\n## Prioritization Process\n\nCloud service providers who receive prioritization under this criteria will follow a separate process similar to the FedRAMP 20x Phase One pilot:\n\n* Cloud service providers who meet this criteria should reach out directly to the FedRAMP Director via [pete@fedramp.gov](mailto:pete@fedramp.gov) to discuss next steps.\n* Providers will be required to meet all [Initial Submission Requirements for the 20x Phase One pilot](/20x/phase-one).\n* Providers will receive additional pre-submission support from FedRAMP.\n* 20xP1 pilot submissions will be accepted outside the standard submission window; there is no deadline for submission.\n* Providers will receive additional post-authorization support from FedRAMP and the FedRAMP Board to encourage adoption.\n\n## List of Prioritized Services\n\n### [ChatGPT Enterprise and API Platform, by OpenAI](https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2533155773)\n\n* *On track for FedRAMP 20x Low authorization by January 2026*\n\n### [Gemini for Government, by Google](https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604952026)\n\n* *On track for FedRAMP 20x Low authorization by January 2026*\n\n### [Perplexity Enterprise Pro for Government, by Perplexity AI, Inc.](https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604643715)\n\n* *On track for FedRAMP 20x Low authorization by January 2026*\n\nAdditional services will be added to this list as they meet the prioritization criteria and begin working on FedRAMP 20x.\n\n[![GSA logo](/gsa-star-mark-whtlogo.svg)](https://www.gsa.gov/)\n\nFedRAMP.gov\n\nAn official website of the GSA’s [Technology Transformation Services](https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/organization/federal-acquisition-service/technology-transformation-services)\n\nLooking for U.S. government information and services?\n\n[Visit USA.gov](https://www.usa.gov/)\n\n Top","content_length":3243,"links":[{"text":"Initial Submission Requirements for the 20x Phase One pilot","url":"https://www.fedramp.gov/20x/phase-one"},{"text":"ChatGPT Enterprise and API Platform, by OpenAI","url":"https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2533155773"},{"text":"Gemini for Government, by Google","url":"https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604952026"},{"text":"Perplexity Enterprise Pro for Government, by Perplexity AI, Inc.","url":"https://marketplace.fedramp.gov/products/FR2604643715"},{"text":"Technology Transformation Services","url":"https://www.gsa.gov/about-us/organization/federal-acquisition-service/technology-transformation-services"},{"text":"Visit USA.gov","url":"https://www.usa.gov/"}]},"isError":false},"status":"completed","startTime":1771633656075,"endTime":1771633657609,"duration":1534,"timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:27:37.609Z"},{"id":"toolu_bdrk_01B8sswHA79jwkApUVcF3n13","name":"web_fetch","tool":"web_fetch","toolName":"web_fetch","serverId":"openagentic_web","serverName":"openagentic_web","executedOn":"mcp-proxy","arguments":{"url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","max_length":50000},"result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"cached\":false,\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework\",\"title\":\"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST\",\"content\":\"[![Circular design includes elements of the AI Risk Management Framework: Govern, Measure, Manage, Map.](/sites/default/files/styles/thumbnail/public/images/2023/01/25/RMF-redesign-rounded-other_graphics-04.png?itok=q6XNzk9H)](/news-events/news/2023/01/nist-risk-management-framework-aims-improve-trustworthiness-artificial)\\n\\nNew guidance seeks to cultivate trust in AI technologies and promote AI innovation while mitigating risk.\",\"content_length\":431,\"links\":[{\"text\":\"Skip to main content\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework#main-content\"},{\"text\":\"Information Technology Laboratory\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl\"},{\"text\":\"Download the AI RMF 1.0\",\"url\":\"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf\"},{\"text\":\"View the AI RMF Playbook\",\"url\":\"https://airc.nist.gov/airmf-resources/playbook/\"},{\"text\":\"Visit the AI Resource Center\",\"url\":\"https://airc.nist.gov/\"},{\"text\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)\",\"url\":\"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.AI.100-1\"},{\"text\":\"workshops\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/artificial-intelligence/nist-ai-engagement\"},{\"text\":\"Fact Sheet\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/document/about-nist-ai-rmf\"},{\"text\":\"NIST AI RMF Playbook\",\"url\":\"https://airc.nist.gov/AI_RMF_Knowledge_Base/Playbook\"},{\"text\":\"AI RMF Roadmap\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/roadmap-nist-artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai\"},{\"text\":\"AI RMF Crosswalk\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/crosswalks-nist-artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework\"},{\"text\":\"Perspectives\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/perspectives-about-nist-artificial-intelligence-risk-management\"},{\"text\":\"Trustworthy and Responsible AI Resource Center\",\"url\":\"https://airc.nist.gov/Home\"},{\"text\":\"AIRC’s Use Case page\",\"url\":\"https://airc.nist.gov/Usecases\"},{\"text\":\"NIST-AI-600-1, Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework: Generative Artificial Intelligence\",\"url\":\"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.AI.600-1\"},{\"text\":\"AI RMF Development\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/ai-rmf-development\"},{\"text\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.ara.pdf\"},{\"text\":\"NIST AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.jpn.pdf\"},{\"text\":\"Second draft of the AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/document/ai-risk-management-framework-2nd-draft\"},{\"text\":\"Initial draft of the AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/document/ai-risk-management-framework-initial-draft\"},{\"text\":\"Concept paper to help guide development of the AI Risk Management Framework\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/document/airmfconceptpaper\"},{\"text\":\"Brief summary\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/document/summary-analysis-responses-nist-artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai-rmf\"},{\"text\":\"responses\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/comments-received-rfi-artificial-intelligence-risk-management\"},{\"text\":\"Draft -Taxonomy of AI Risk\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/document/draft-taxonomy-ai-risk-october-15-2021\"},{\"text\":\"AI Risk Management Framework Request for Information\",\"url\":\"https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2021/07/29/2021-16176/artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework\"},{\"text\":\"Was this page helpful?\",\"url\":\"https://www.nist.gov/webform/page_feedback?page=https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework&page_title=AI Risk Management Framework&source_entity_type=node&source_entity_id=1674601\"}]}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"cached":false,"url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework","title":"AI Risk Management Framework | NIST","content":"[![Circular design includes elements of the AI Risk Management Framework: Govern, Measure, Manage, Map.](/sites/default/files/styles/thumbnail/public/images/2023/01/25/RMF-redesign-rounded-other_graphics-04.png?itok=q6XNzk9H)](/news-events/news/2023/01/nist-risk-management-framework-aims-improve-trustworthiness-artificial)\n\nNew guidance seeks to cultivate trust in AI technologies and promote AI innovation while mitigating risk.","content_length":431,"links":[{"text":"Skip to main content","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework#main-content"},{"text":"Information Technology Laboratory","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl"},{"text":"Download the AI RMF 1.0","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.pdf"},{"text":"View the AI RMF Playbook","url":"https://airc.nist.gov/airmf-resources/playbook/"},{"text":"Visit the AI Resource Center","url":"https://airc.nist.gov/"},{"text":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)","url":"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.AI.100-1"},{"text":"workshops","url":"https://www.nist.gov/artificial-intelligence/nist-ai-engagement"},{"text":"Fact Sheet","url":"https://www.nist.gov/document/about-nist-ai-rmf"},{"text":"NIST AI RMF Playbook","url":"https://airc.nist.gov/AI_RMF_Knowledge_Base/Playbook"},{"text":"AI RMF Roadmap","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/roadmap-nist-artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework-ai"},{"text":"AI RMF Crosswalk","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/crosswalks-nist-artificial-intelligence-risk-management-framework"},{"text":"Perspectives","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/perspectives-about-nist-artificial-intelligence-risk-management"},{"text":"Trustworthy and Responsible AI Resource Center","url":"https://airc.nist.gov/Home"},{"text":"AIRC’s Use Case page","url":"https://airc.nist.gov/Usecases"},{"text":"NIST-AI-600-1, Artificial Intelligence Risk Management Framework: Generative Artificial Intelligence","url":"https://doi.org/10.6028/NIST.AI.600-1"},{"text":"AI RMF Development","url":"https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework/ai-rmf-development"},{"text":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.ara.pdf"},{"text":"NIST AI Risk Management Framework","url":"https://nvlpubs.nist.gov/nistpubs/ai/NIST.AI.100-1.jpn.pdf"},{"text":"Second draft of the AI Risk Management Framework","url":"https://www.nist.gov/document/ai-risk-management-framework-2nd-draft"},{"text":"Initial draft of the AI Risk Management Framework","url":"https://www.nist.gov/document/ai-risk-management-framework-initial-draft"},{"text":"Concept paper to help guide development of the AI Risk Management Framework","url":"h