event: tool_executing
data: {"name":"web_store_knowledge","arguments":{"title":"FedRAMP AI/ML Authorization Requirements & NIST AI RMF — Live Research (Feb 2026)","content":"## FedRAMP AI Prioritization (Effective August 18, 2025)\n\n### Source: https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/ (fetched 2026-02-21)\n\nFedRAMP now formally prioritizes AI cloud services for authorization under the FedRAMP 20x program. This was triggered by CIO Council recommendation (Aug 12, 2025) and FedRAMP Board electronic vote.\n\n### Prioritization Criteria (ALL must be met):\n1. Enterprise-grade features: SSO, SCIM provisioning, RBAC, real-time analytics\n2. Data separation guarantee: customer training data cannot leave customer environment without authorization\n3. Demand: at least 5 CFO Act agencies OR specific CIO Council recommendation\n4. Available via GSA Multiple Award Schedule\n5. Able to meet FedRAMP 20x requirements within 2 months of acceptance\n\n### Currently Prioritized Services (as of Feb 2026):\n- ChatGPT Enterprise & API Platform (OpenAI) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\n- Gemini for Government (Google) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\n- Perplexity Enterprise Pro for Government (Perplexity AI) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\n\n### Process:\n- CSPs contact FedRAMP Director (pete@fedramp.gov) directly\n- Must meet 20x Phase One pilot initial submission requirements\n- Submissions accepted outside standard windows (no deadline)\n- Additional pre- and post-authorization support provided\n\n---\n\n## FedRAMP 2026 Changes (Source: ignyteplatform.com, Dec 2025)\n\nKey 2026 developments identified from article structure:\n1. FedRAMP 20x Phase 2 expansion (eligibility at fedramp.gov/20x/phase-two/participate/)\n2. Possible 20x Phase 3 trial\n3. Significant Change Requests → Significant Change Notifications (RFC 0007)\n4. Minimum Assessment Standard implementation\n5. Better reciprocity with Authorized Data Sharing\n6. Enhanced Continuous Monitoring (ConMon) requirements\n7. Recommended Secure Configurations\n8. Potential NIST SP 800-53 r5 update (release 5.2.0 referenced)\n\n---\n\n## NIST AI Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)\n\n### Source: https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework (fetched 2026-02-21)\n\n### Key Documents:\n- AI RMF 1.0 (NIST.AI.100-1) — released January 2023, core framework\n- NIST-AI-600-1 — Generative AI Profile, released July 26, 2024\n- AI RMF Playbook — implementation guidance at airc.nist.gov\n- AI RMF Roadmap — forward-looking development plan\n- AI RMF Crosswalk — mapping to other frameworks\n\n### Four Core Functions:\n1. GOVERN — AI governance and accountability (maps to FedRAMP PM-9, PM-28)\n2. MAP — Context and risk framing (maps to FedRAMP RA-3, RA-5)\n3. MEASURE — Risk analysis and monitoring (maps to FedRAMP CA-7, SI-4)\n4. MANAGE — Risk response and mitigation (maps to FedRAMP IR-4, IR-6)\n\n### Resources:\n- Trustworthy & Responsible AI Resource Center: airc.nist.gov\n- AI RMF Playbook: airc.nist.gov/AI_RMF_Knowledge_Base/Playbook\n- Use Cases: airc.nist.gov/Usecases\n- Taxonomy of AI Risk: nist.gov/document/draft-taxonomy-ai-risk-october-15-2021\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaway for OpenAgentic Platform\n\nThe convergence of FedRAMP 20x AI prioritization + NIST AI RMF + NIST-AI-600-1 GenAI Profile creates a concrete compliance pathway:\n- 20x Low authorization is the fastest path for conversational AI services\n- NIST AI RMF's GOVERN/MAP/MEASURE/MANAGE maps directly to FedRAMP control families\n- Model drift monitoring (MEASURE function) remains critical for ConMon\n- Data separation is a hard requirement — training data isolation must be provable\n- First 3 AI authorizations (OpenAI, Google, Perplexity) expected by Jan 2026","source_url":"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/","tags":["FedRAMP","AI","ML","NIST","AI-RMF","20x","authorization","compliance","2025","2026","GenAI","governance"],"importance":"high"},"toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01Xa4UwJyjovqmBHkNw12WW9","targetServer":"openagentic_web","timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:28:25.288Z"}

event: tool_result
data: {"name":"web_store_knowledge","result":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\"success\":true,\"message\":\"Knowledge stored: FedRAMP AI/ML Authorization Requirements & NIST AI RMF — Live Research (Feb 2026)\",\"entry\":{\"title\":\"FedRAMP AI/ML Authorization Requirements & NIST AI RMF — Live Research (Feb 2026)\",\"content\":\"## FedRAMP AI Prioritization (Effective August 18, 2025)\\n\\n### Source: https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/ (fetched 2026-02-21)\\n\\nFedRAMP now formally prioritizes AI cloud services for authorization under the FedRAMP 20x program. This was triggered by CIO Council recommendation (Aug 12, 2025) and FedRAMP Board electronic vote.\\n\\n### Prioritization Criteria (ALL must be met):\\n1. Enterprise-grade features: SSO, SCIM provisioning, RBAC, real-time analytics\\n2. Data separation guarantee: customer training data cannot leave customer environment without authorization\\n3. Demand: at least 5 CFO Act agencies OR specific CIO Council recommendation\\n4. Available via GSA Multiple Award Schedule\\n5. Able to meet FedRAMP 20x requirements within 2 months of acceptance\\n\\n### Currently Prioritized Services (as of Feb 2026):\\n- ChatGPT Enterprise & API Platform (OpenAI) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\\n- Gemini for Government (Google) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\\n- Perplexity Enterprise Pro for Government (Perplexity AI) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\\n\\n### Process:\\n- CSPs contact FedRAMP Director (pete@fedramp.gov) directly\\n- Must meet 20x Phase One pilot initial submission requirements\\n- Submissions accepted outside standard windows (no deadline)\\n- Additional pre- and post-authorization support provided\\n\\n---\\n\\n## FedRAMP 2026 Changes (Source: ignyteplatform.com, Dec 2025)\\n\\nKey 2026 developments identified from article structure:\\n1. FedRAMP 20x Phase 2 expansion (eligibility at fedramp.gov/20x/phase-two/participate/)\\n2. Possible 20x Phase 3 trial\\n3. Significant Change Requests → Significant Change Notifications (RFC 0007)\\n4. Minimum Assessment Standard implementation\\n5. Better reciprocity with Authorized Data Sharing\\n6. Enhanced Continuous Monitoring (ConMon) requirements\\n7. Recommended Secure Configurations\\n8. Potential NIST SP 800-53 r5 update (release 5.2.0 referenced)\\n\\n---\\n\\n## NIST AI Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)\\n\\n### Source: https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework (fetched 2026-02-21)\\n\\n### Key Documents:\\n- AI RMF 1.0 (NIST.AI.100-1) — released January 2023, core framework\\n- NIST-AI-600-1 — Generative AI Profile, released July 26, 2024\\n- AI RMF Playbook — implementation guidance at airc.nist.gov\\n- AI RMF Roadmap — forward-looking development plan\\n- AI RMF Crosswalk — mapping to other frameworks\\n\\n### Four Core Functions:\\n1. GOVERN — AI governance and accountability (maps to FedRAMP PM-9, PM-28)\\n2. MAP — Context and risk framing (maps to FedRAMP RA-3, RA-5)\\n3. MEASURE — Risk analysis and monitoring (maps to FedRAMP CA-7, SI-4)\\n4. MANAGE — Risk response and mitigation (maps to FedRAMP IR-4, IR-6)\\n\\n### Resources:\\n- Trustworthy & Responsible AI Resource Center: airc.nist.gov\\n- AI RMF Playbook: airc.nist.gov/AI_RMF_Knowledge_Base/Playbook\\n- Use Cases: airc.nist.gov/Usecases\\n- Taxonomy of AI Risk: nist.gov/document/draft-taxonomy-ai-risk-october-15-2021\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Key Takeaway for OpenAgentic Platform\\n\\nThe convergence of FedRAMP 20x AI prioritization + NIST AI RMF + NIST-AI-600-1 GenAI Profile creates a concrete compliance pathway:\\n- 20x Low authorization is the fastest path for conversational AI services\\n- NIST AI RMF's GOVERN/MAP/MEASURE/MANAGE maps directly to FedRAMP control families\\n- Model drift monitoring (MEASURE function) remains critical for ConMon\\n- Data separation is a hard requirement — training data isolation must be provable\\n- First 3 AI authorizations (OpenAI, Google, Perplexity) expected by Jan 2026\",\"source\":\"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/\",\"tags\":[\"FedRAMP\",\"AI\",\"ML\",\"NIST\",\"AI-RMF\",\"20x\",\"authorization\",\"compliance\",\"2025\",\"2026\",\"GenAI\",\"governance\"],\"importance\":\"high\",\"type\":\"web_research\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-02-21T00:28:25.308205\"},\"note\":\"This information is now available for future reference\"}"}],"structuredContent":{"success":true,"message":"Knowledge stored: FedRAMP AI/ML Authorization Requirements & NIST AI RMF — Live Research (Feb 2026)","entry":{"title":"FedRAMP AI/ML Authorization Requirements & NIST AI RMF — Live Research (Feb 2026)","content":"## FedRAMP AI Prioritization (Effective August 18, 2025)\n\n### Source: https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/ (fetched 2026-02-21)\n\nFedRAMP now formally prioritizes AI cloud services for authorization under the FedRAMP 20x program. This was triggered by CIO Council recommendation (Aug 12, 2025) and FedRAMP Board electronic vote.\n\n### Prioritization Criteria (ALL must be met):\n1. Enterprise-grade features: SSO, SCIM provisioning, RBAC, real-time analytics\n2. Data separation guarantee: customer training data cannot leave customer environment without authorization\n3. Demand: at least 5 CFO Act agencies OR specific CIO Council recommendation\n4. Available via GSA Multiple Award Schedule\n5. Able to meet FedRAMP 20x requirements within 2 months of acceptance\n\n### Currently Prioritized Services (as of Feb 2026):\n- ChatGPT Enterprise & API Platform (OpenAI) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\n- Gemini for Government (Google) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\n- Perplexity Enterprise Pro for Government (Perplexity AI) — on track for 20x Low auth by Jan 2026\n\n### Process:\n- CSPs contact FedRAMP Director (pete@fedramp.gov) directly\n- Must meet 20x Phase One pilot initial submission requirements\n- Submissions accepted outside standard windows (no deadline)\n- Additional pre- and post-authorization support provided\n\n---\n\n## FedRAMP 2026 Changes (Source: ignyteplatform.com, Dec 2025)\n\nKey 2026 developments identified from article structure:\n1. FedRAMP 20x Phase 2 expansion (eligibility at fedramp.gov/20x/phase-two/participate/)\n2. Possible 20x Phase 3 trial\n3. Significant Change Requests → Significant Change Notifications (RFC 0007)\n4. Minimum Assessment Standard implementation\n5. Better reciprocity with Authorized Data Sharing\n6. Enhanced Continuous Monitoring (ConMon) requirements\n7. Recommended Secure Configurations\n8. Potential NIST SP 800-53 r5 update (release 5.2.0 referenced)\n\n---\n\n## NIST AI Risk Management Framework (AI RMF)\n\n### Source: https://www.nist.gov/itl/ai-risk-management-framework (fetched 2026-02-21)\n\n### Key Documents:\n- AI RMF 1.0 (NIST.AI.100-1) — released January 2023, core framework\n- NIST-AI-600-1 — Generative AI Profile, released July 26, 2024\n- AI RMF Playbook — implementation guidance at airc.nist.gov\n- AI RMF Roadmap — forward-looking development plan\n- AI RMF Crosswalk — mapping to other frameworks\n\n### Four Core Functions:\n1. GOVERN — AI governance and accountability (maps to FedRAMP PM-9, PM-28)\n2. MAP — Context and risk framing (maps to FedRAMP RA-3, RA-5)\n3. MEASURE — Risk analysis and monitoring (maps to FedRAMP CA-7, SI-4)\n4. MANAGE — Risk response and mitigation (maps to FedRAMP IR-4, IR-6)\n\n### Resources:\n- Trustworthy & Responsible AI Resource Center: airc.nist.gov\n- AI RMF Playbook: airc.nist.gov/AI_RMF_Knowledge_Base/Playbook\n- Use Cases: airc.nist.gov/Usecases\n- Taxonomy of AI Risk: nist.gov/document/draft-taxonomy-ai-risk-october-15-2021\n\n---\n\n## Key Takeaway for OpenAgentic Platform\n\nThe convergence of FedRAMP 20x AI prioritization + NIST AI RMF + NIST-AI-600-1 GenAI Profile creates a concrete compliance pathway:\n- 20x Low authorization is the fastest path for conversational AI services\n- NIST AI RMF's GOVERN/MAP/MEASURE/MANAGE maps directly to FedRAMP control families\n- Model drift monitoring (MEASURE function) remains critical for ConMon\n- Data separation is a hard requirement — training data isolation must be provable\n- First 3 AI authorizations (OpenAI, Google, Perplexity) expected by Jan 2026","source":"https://www.fedramp.gov/ai/","tags":["FedRAMP","AI","ML","NIST","AI-RMF","20x","authorization","compliance","2025","2026","GenAI","governance"],"importance":"high","type":"web_research","timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:28:25.308205"},"note":"This information is now available for future reference"},"isError":false},"toolCallId":"toolu_bdrk_01Xa4UwJyjovqmBHkNw12WW9","executionTimeMs":26,"targetServer":"openagentic_web","timestamp":"2026-02-21T00:28:25.336Z"}

